[INTERPRETER]
{"action": "explain", "question": "How hard should Z4 feel?", "free_text": "How hard should Z4 feel? I'm not sure I'm pushing enough."}

JOSI:
Z4 should feel hard but controlled — you can squeeze out a few words, but not hold a conversation. Your breathing is heavy, your legs are working. If you can chat comfortably, push a bit more. If you're gasping and can't maintain the effort for the full interval, back off a notch. The sweet spot is strong and sustainable.

